Package: consumeR
Type: Package
Title: Transparent and Reproducible Consumer Research Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Josh", "Gonzales",
           email = "joshgonzalesphd@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8633-3380"))
    )
Description: Provides transparent, well-documented functions for consumer research
    analysis that facilitate reproducibility during peer review. All functions are
    designed with clarity and readability in mind using tidyverse principles, making
    code easy to understand for reviewers with varying levels of programming experience.
    Includes descriptive statistics, group comparisons, reliability analysis (Cronbach's
    alpha, composite reliability, AVE), and factor analysis (EFA/CFA) with beautiful
    ggplot2 visualizations. Functions include clear documentation, sensible defaults,
    and extensive examples.
